Program: The Forum
Title: Codes and ciphers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02j48c0
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 Feb 2015
Is your mobile phone ‘leaking’ data even though the encryption tools it uses are mathematically perfect? Will quantum computing spell the end of online payments? And could cryptocurrencies, such as Bitcoin, be the banking revolution which the developing world needs? Bridget Kendall talks to cryptographer Maire O’Neill, philosopher Luciano Floridi and financial journalist Paul Vigna. (Photo: Digital binary code background. Credit: Shan Pillay) Show less